The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 April is 41,604 (4,815.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 April, there were 135 new confirmed cases (15.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 April, there were 154 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 12% (19 fewer cases).
